1. Sign Up for GitHub:  
   - Go to GitHub.  
   - Click on "Sign up".  
   - Enter your email, create a password, and choose a username.   

2. Create a Repository:  
   - Click the "+" icon (top-right corner) and select "New repository".  
   - Enter a repository name.  
   - Choose the repository visibility. 
   - Click "Create repository".  

3. Add Folders to the Repository:  
   - Go to your repository page.  
   - Click on the "Add file" dropdown and select "Create new file".  
   - In the file name box, type the folder name followed by a slash.   
   - Click "Commit new file" after creating each folder.  
